BOE’s Dale Says It’s a Risk That U.K. Manufacturing Will Slow

-- B y   S c o t t   H a m i l t o n
-- 
2011-09-21T12:15:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/boe-s-dale-says-it-s-a-risk-that-u-k-manufacturing-will-slow.html
Bank of  England  Chief Economist
 Spencer Dale  said there’s a risk that U.K. factory production
will weaken as the global economy falters.  “Exports have been aided by pretty strong recovery in
world demand and a lower pound,” he said in answer to audience
questions after a speech today in South Shields, England. “But
it is a challenge is whether exports and manufacturing grow with
the slowdown in world demand.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Hamilton in London at 
 shamilton8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
